Always by hand, never by prompt.

In the beginning of my career, I would have to convince others that my digital painting style was a legitimate art form. Something that I was creatively in control of, by hand and not by a magic button that generated a beautiful image. My work has been and always will be a product of the journey I took to get there. It is anxiously looking at a blank piece of paper for the answers, it is the building anticipation as I get an idea started, it is problem solving the failures, it is celebrating the victories. Art is taking an idea and putting it through the human machine. One that is full of wonderful emotions, inspirations, experiences and unique voices that only the artist can interpret and place onto the canvas. 

A.I. starts with a keyword and ends seconds later with hollow images, devoid of the human process and based solely on stolen creativity. I have no issue with A.I. as a novelty, but at it’s current state it steals from the past and takes away from our future.

#endjourney #humanart #artnotai #artisticprocess #noprompts

My art is my voice and I want to thank everyone that has allowed me to continue to tell my unique story through this creative process. Art is so much more than what shows up on a gallery wall or your social feed. It’s a complex story that begins with an artist’s passions, fears, failures and triumphs and continues with your experience in how you connect with the work. Art is a journey we take together and one that has an everlasting human connection. Here’s to many more journeys together for years to come! Thanks again and Happy New Years!

New piece I created for my lovely friends over at @archenemyarts for their 11th anniversary show. If your in Philly, the opening is tonight. Otherwise, check them out online to see all the amazing work that is hanging!

My brain went on a roller coaster creating this imagery. Good vs evil, multidimensional theories, science vs religion, eternal struggles, etc, etc… but I didn’t put all the pieces together until I was listening to Courtney Love scream the lyrics “One above and one below” while I was in the car. Sometimes inspiration hits you when your not looking for it, but I’m always happy when it shows up 😁

This piece is available through the gallery.

It’s Halloween and I figured I’d share the full cover art I created for this years @ruemorguemag Halloween issue and the demons that inspired it.

For most artists, the scariest monster this year has been AI. This modern day vampire feeds on centuries of human created art, trying to replicate something it knows nothing about… life. So, while humans rely on complex emotions as a part of the creative process, AI is simply a parasite that wears a skin and assumes an identity. 

This cover concept was pulled directly from my personal database of human emotions, not from prompts. I relied of my love of horror movies, the fears of being replaced, my anger towards those who steal for profit and my sorrow for the next generation of creatives that will face an uphill battle just to have their voices heard. This is a self portrait that represents every human artist that pours their entire existence into their work and the machine that feeds off of it.

Artwork like this wouldn’t be possible either without those that support the arts like @ruemorguemag and the humans I get to work with. Thanks @necromandrea for helping me see this one through from sketch to final!
